\"mocked construction\\\");\\n        } catch (InvocationTargetException exception) {\\n            rethrowUnlessUnsupportedFeatureError(exception.getCause());\\n        } catch (Error error) {\\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\\n                throw error;\\n            }\\n        } finally {\\n            currentThread.setContextClassLoader(previousContextClassLoader);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static String exerciseConstructionMockWithInlineMockMaker() {\\n        try (MockedConstruction<ConstructedGreeting> mockedConstruction =\\n                Mockito.mockConstruction(\\n                        ConstructedGreeting.class,\\n                        (mock, context) -> {\\n                            Constructor<?> constructor = context.constructor();\\n\\n                            verifyConstructionContext(context, constructor);\\n                            when(mock.message()).thenReturn(\\\"mocked construction\\\");\\n                        })) {\\n            ConstructedGreeting greeting =\\n                    new ConstructedGreeting(\\\"Mockito\\\", 5, new GreetingFormat(\\\"Hello\\\"));\\n\\n            if (!\\\"mocked construction\\\".equals(greeting.message())) {\\n                throw new AssertionError(\\\"Constructed mock did not use the configured answer\\\");\\n            }\\n            if (!mockedConstruction.constructed().equals(List.of(greeting))) {\\n                throw new AssertionError(\\\"Constructed mocks were not recorded\\\");\\n            }\\n            return greeting.message();\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static void verifyConstructionContext(\\n            MockedConstruction.Context context, Constructor<?> constructor) {\\n        if (context.getCount() != 1) {\\n            throw new AssertionError(\\\"Unexpected construction count: \\\" + context.getCount());\\n        }\\n        if (!context.arguments().equals(List.of(\\\"Mockito\\\", 5, new GreetingFormat(\\\"